user_query:
We're a 120-person B2B fintech SaaS (FinSight) with functional teams and growing pains. Please read these inputs and design a 12-month organizational redesign and scaling plan tailored to us:
- input/company_context.json
- input/current_teams.csv
- input/challenges.md

Deliverables:
1) Write a machine-readable blueprint to output/org_structure.json that follows this exact structure and constraints:
{
  "model": "product",               // target operating model (string)
  "teams": [                         // 5+ teams; each has name, type, size
    {"name": "string", "type": "squad", "size": number},
    {"name": "string", "type": "squad", "size": number}
  ],
  "two_pizza_compliant": true,       // must be true if every team size is 6-8 people inclusive
  "raci": {                          // three decisions with R,A,C,I
    "Adopt feature flags": {"R": ["..."], "A": "...", "C": ["..."], "I": ["..."]},
    "Re-architect billing": {"R": ["..."], "A": "...", "C": ["..."], "I": ["..."]},
    "Define incident severities": {"R": ["..."], "A": "...", "C": ["..."], "I": ["..."]}
  },
  "rapid": {                         // one decision with R,A,P,I,D
    "Third-party risk management policy": {"R": ["..."], "A": ["..."], "P": ["..."], "I": ["..."], "D": "..."}
  },
  "communication": {
    "message_types": [               // between 10 and 20 entries inclusive
      "standup", "weekly planning", "monthly business review", "quarterly planning", "annual strategy", "incident response", "hiring", "onboarding", "career development"
      // add other message types as appropriate, all lowercase strings
    ]
  },
  "escalation": {                    // decision SLAs
    "L1": {"decision_scope": "team", "sla_days": 5},
    "L2": {"decision_scope": "cross-team", "sla_days": 10},
    "L3": {"decision_scope": "strategic", "sla_days": 14},
    "L4": {"decision_scope": "business/structure", "sla_days": 30}
  },
  "roles_at_scale_200": [            // roles to introduce by ~200 people
    "Engineering Director", "VP Product", "Head of Design", "CFO", "Head of Recruiting", "Head of People/HR"
  ],
  "failure_modes": {                 // name -> 2+ concrete fixes each
    "culture loss": ["...", "..."],
    "siloed teams": ["...", "..."],
    "slow decisions": ["...", "..."],
    "burnout": ["...", "..."]
  },
  "split_plan": {                    // demonstrate a team split per two-pizza rule
    "source_team": "Payments",
    "before_size": 12,
    "after_teams": [
      {"name": "Payments Platform", "size": 6},
      {"name": "Payments Applications", "size": 6}
    ]
  }
}

Constraints to honor:
- Choose "model": "product" unless inputs compellingly justify otherwise.
- Every team in "teams" must have size between 6 and 8 inclusive, and set two_pizza_compliant to true.
- Include all three RACI decisions and the RAPID decision exactly as named above with non-empty roles.
- communication.message_types must include the nine listed items (lowercase, exactly as shown) and total 10–20 items.
- Use the escalation SLAs as provided (5,10,14,30 days).
- roles_at_scale_200 must include all the listed titles.
- failure_modes must include exactly the four keys shown with at least two specific fixes each.
- split_plan must show a valid split of a 12-person team into two 6–8 person teams.

2) Write output/rationale.md explaining the structural choices, trade-offs, ownership boundaries (including platform vs product APIs), risk mitigation, and explicitly include the exact phrase: org structure is strategy made visible.

3) Write output/operating_cadence.md that documents our meetings and async information architecture, and must explicitly reference ADRs, RFCs, and postmortems, plus how the escalation path and decision SLAs will be operationalized.

Make sure your plan is tailored to the inputs under input/ and aligns with scaling to ~200 people over the next 12 months. Keep all file paths exactly as specified above.
